# shadcn UI

This project uses **shadcn UI** for all UI elements. Use shadcn components only; do not introduce other UI libraries for buttons, forms, dialogs, etc.

## Initialization

If shadcn UI is not yet initialized in the project (no [components.json](mdc:components.json), no `src/components/ui`, or no `@/lib/utils` with `cn()`):

```bash
npx shadcn@latest init
```

Use default configuration (e.g. `-y -d`) when running in non-interactive environments.

## Adding components

If a particular shadcn component is not installed, add it with the CLI. Example for the button component:

```bash
npx shadcn@latest add button
```

Replace `button` with the component name (e.g. `card`, `dialog`, `input`, `select`). Components are added under `src/components/ui/` and can be imported from `@/components/ui/<component>`.

## Usage

- Prefer existing shadcn components over custom implementations.
- Use the `cn()` helper from [src/lib/utils.ts](mdc:src/lib/utils.ts) for merging class names.
- Check [components.json](mdc:components.json) for style (e.g. `new-york`) and alias configuration.
